ratings.rComments: She is sweet, respected, and helpful person who gives examples and explain about the concepts. She loves to hear questions and curious to hear from students' voices. The are no exams but weekly online open-notes quizzes and a final. Better go to lectures because she gives you the rest of the notes to ace the quizzes and assignments. She's awesome.

Go to class and study for the final and you'll do fine. Attendance isn't mandatory but otherwise you won't get the notes. No tests throughout the semester except online quizzes, and then a cumulative exam at the end. No textbook.

There is a ton of extra credit, and she makes lecture really fun and interactive. She gets to know a lot of students on a personal level as well. The content is thick & somewhat tricky but there are no midterms. I did all the extra credit and went into the final with a 106%. Easy easy A.

You don't even need to show up to lecture to pass this class. There is a ton of extra credit, and she makes lecture really fun and interactive. She gets to know a lot of students on a personal level as well. The content is thick & somewhat tricky but there are no midterms. I did all the extra credit and went into the final with a 106%. Easy easy A.

Decent professor who will teach you what you need to know for the tests and quizzes. The people on here who said her FSHN101 is tough must be out of their minds. It's easily one of easiest classes I've ever taken. All you do is show up and listen to the lecture and take notes. There's not even a textbook. My kind of class and my kind of professor.

The content is easy enough, but the professor is kind of stuck up when you talk to her. Not all grades were posted on compass before final grades were out, so at the very end of the course i thought I got an A but ended up failing because something went wrong with compass& online quizzes. No help from the professor, she didn't seem to care one bit.

Everything that is on the exams is in the notes. Since there is no textbook for this class, notes are a must and she does not post them online. Dr. Bohn is very helpful and knowledgeable about food science, and is happy to discuss it with you outside of class in office hours. TONS of extra credit is offered and you can leave with over 100% easily.

for a gen ed, content is very dry and boring. pretty hard for a gen ed. i would rather have a textbook and teach myself then sit through these long tedious lectures. quizzes are easy, where exams aren't relevent to lectures.  If your looking for a class like this, take FSHN 120. way easier and more interestiing.

Thought she would be nice, kind of snotty actually. Not someone whose office hours id want to go to. Information not horrible but you have to go to class. Make sure you don't miss a quiz they are alot of points and its not like your lowest is dropped or anything!

Class was ok. Material was very boring. Mostly focuses on food science because she's biased toward it. Couldn't stand her most days because she has a huge ego for being a food scientist.Attendance isn't mandatory but necessary for notes.  Exams were unprofessional settings:  very distracting, TAs talking a lot, etc.

I don't know what these people are talking about. The class is pretty boring in general but the content is so easy. The quizzes are easy points and she drops your lowest exam grade. I didn't even have to take the final. She's not the most helpful but if you're looking for an easy gen ed this is the class for you.

This class isn't that hard but the professor is annoying and notes are too tedious. she isn't understanding whatsoever. I had a death in the family and she wouldn't let me make up my exam but yet she didn't have the exam grades up because the basketball players hadn't taken it yet. ridiculous.
Worst ever
terrible teacher. if you miss a class, getting notes is nearly impossible. tests are tricky and lectures are a nightmare. avoid this class. worst class i've taken. especially since it's a gen ed.

Terrible prof and class. You don't learn anything in lecture. There is a ridiculous amount of material and what you are tested on is really not what you learn. She is a terrible lecturer. I would avoid by all means.

You don't learn anything in lecture except the fill in the blank answers. The review guides are at least twice as long as the tests and basically cover everything in the notes so they don't narrow down anything. In addition, even if you feel you know the review guide you could still do very poorly on the tests. Overall, easy minus class minus tests

This class is horrible. The study guides do nothing to help for the tests. The tests are horribly written. Our class average was horrible. It's a 100 level class. You would think if your class is doing that poorly on the exams there's something wrong. Don't take this class, not an easy gen ed at all.
This class is nearly impossible to study for. Boring. Tests are poorly written. I went to office hours and they weren't helpful. Don't take this class.

Gotta agree with the majority here and say a horrible gen Ed class if your looking for one.. Her lectures are insanely boring, and the class avg on test has been 70% for a 100 level class... Study guides are useless as the whole lecture is essentially fair game.. Horrible, avoid if possible

NOT AN EASY GEN ED. If you are looking to fill a science requirement, think again. Despite being a 100 level gen ed, this course requires a great knowledge and understanding of chemistry. I hadn't taken chemistry since high school and was completely thrown off. Very hard to do well on tests if you aren't familiar with chemistry

Although this class isn't hard if you try or care, it is not an easy gened for those just trying to get a science credit (Gened). Bohn isn't a hard professor but slightly annoying. She's obsessed with eating and food. NOT AN EASY GENED!

I LOVE BOHN she is so much fun and upbeat and loves teaching. This class was so easy I never went to class and got an A. She tells you what will be on the tests and the final is optional.People who said the class is hard must have been studying for the wrong class!

This class was ridiculous. My adviser told me it wouldn't be too difficult, but I have never done so poorly on tests at UIUC as I did in this class. The questions are very tricky and specific- I spent hours studying and only managed to pull off a C on some. Bohn is also sore on the ears- expect to fall asleep in class (if you even go that is).

Ok, I heard this class was an easy A. But you actually have to work for your grade in this class. Honestly, the tests this semester were impossible. If you go to lecture you should be able to pull at leaast a C on the test, but that would be if she talked about the content of the notes instead of candy burgers and other nonsense.
This is a great class if you need it as a Gened, otherwise not very interesting. Mrs. Bohn is cool but the class is challenging at all.

her high pitched voice makes me want to throw up. She shushes the class like your a preschooler. This is NOT an easy A because you actually have to study way to much for such an easy class. Thought it was going to be easy only to get screwed over on tests.

Awful woman. Terribly annoying and just spews a TON of completely useless information for an hour straight. Her tests are terribly written. Her voice lead me out of class within the first 20 mins on several occasions. Not an easy A gened....Don't put yourself through it.

Horrible teacher, she sounds like a dying cat when she speaks and is shushing the class the whole time. i took this class for an easy A only to find out that the tests were really HARD. if you do everything else right and do pretty bad on the tests like i did, youll get a B, which is what i have. FML

very easy to get a A class. she teach very well and make it very easy to understand if you pay attention on it. extra credit are easy. this is a fun class. recommend for student to take it as a gen ed.

Very interesting class, and easy A. Dr. Bohn knows her stuff and makes the class interesting. Even though attendance was not mandatory, I only missed a few classes because everything was so interesting.  She's very knowledgeable and passionate about this field... very refreshing. Exams are basically memorizing notes, but much of it is common sense.

This class is not great at all. You can get an A in the class you just need to study and memorize all the useless information that is in the notes. The information can be lengthy at times. The professor is annoying and is shushing the class about 99% of the time. Take it for an A, but not a class that is worth looking forward to go to.
Need an easy physical science ged ed? I'd recommend this class.

I think class is super easy. You have the opportunity to take 5 exams and the top 4 count, but what pisses me off is that you can only be excused from an exam for uiuc sponsored events or RELIGIOUS purposes... yet when I was sick for a month, I HAD TO drag myself to the room, coughing and yacking to take the stupid exam so i wouldnt take the final

The class class is super easy. However, I've always felt that going to class actually hurt your grades.  Dawn is a horrible teacher who teaches in a confusing manner and does a horrible job of relating with students. Did not give us extension on online assignment after the weather knocked out servers the weekend it was due. Just stay at home, easy

She's a decent Professor, seems to really enjoy what she does.  I had a bad semester and still pulled off a C, so if you want to do well attend class and study a few weeks prior to the tests.  There is no book, so lecture attendance is pivotal, even though there is no recording of it.

Don't have to go to lectures. All the notes are online. No textbook, but iClickers are suggested. She gave us extra credit at the end of the year just for registering them. Pretty easy class... I still went to lecture because it was kind of interesting sometimes. Easy class, but I did learn some cool stuff. I'd recommend it.
The class is super easy. You don't have to go to class since the lectures are online and you print them off. All she does is read from the lecture notes, not really teach.
Boring, but easy. Didn't bother going to class much and still got an A.
No Comments
